v2: Income: Burdín, Gabriel; Esponda, Fernando and Vigorito, Andrea (2013). Inequality and Top Incomes in Uruguay: A comparison between household surveys and income tax micro-data. WTID Working Paper 2014/1. Series updated by G. Burdín, M. de Rosa, and A. Vigorito.

v19: Consumer price index from www.ine.gub.uy, average for year t.
v44: The Pareto-Lorenz a coefficients were computed using the top shares estimates (from the top 0.1% share within the top 1% share): a=1/[1-log(S1%/S0.1%)/log(10)].
v45: The inverted Pareto-Lorenz b coefficients were computed from the Pareto-Lorenz a coefficients using the formula b=a/(a-1). Alternatively they can be computed by using directly the top income shares estimates and the formula: b=1/[log(Skx%/Sx%)/log(k)].
